## 8. Split Book Hub access

### Status

Not started.

### Goal

Keep the Book Hub open for free users, but separate free reading-life tools from full-access learning tools.

### Free Book Hub areas

Free users should be able to use:

* Book Info
* Reading Reflection
* Just Reading timer
* Listening timer
* Basic book tracking
* Finished / DNF / Want to Read / Currently Reading
* Reading-life snapshots

### Full-access Book Hub areas

Full/trial/current students should be able to use:

* Vocab Tools
* Story Notes
* Vocabulary stats
* Study stats
* Flashcard actions
* Saved-word support
* Curiosity Reading links
* Fluid Reading with saved-word support

### Notes

This should be done carefully because the Book Hub likely mixes many UI sections in one file.

